  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Big Issue Lagos: Empowering, informing and training slum-dwellers</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Nigeria&#x2019;s capital Lagos, is home to some of the world&#x2019;s largest slums. Poverty is rife and there is a severe lack of employment, training and education for people on the margins of society. In addition, slum-dwellers/homeless people have limited access to information about their rights and limited ways of making their voices heard. This project will build the capacity of two local organisations to establish another business - Big Issue Lagos. The street paper will provide quality and independent editorial content covering issues of social justice and community interest and acting as a platform for the unheard voices of local slum-dwellers/homeless people. This will provide employment for vendors who buy magazines at a reduced cost and sell at a profit. Appropriate vendor training will be provided to slum-dwellers/ homeless people. During the project period the Big Issue will empower and increase the incomes of hundreds of slum-dwellers/homeless people. It will strengthen civil society and improve the rights of slum-dwellers/homeless people, providing a platform to leverage partners&#x2019; work and raise additional policy issues.</narrative>
  </description>
